# Versioning and changelog

When working on eGOdary, bump the patch version by **+0.0.1** and update `CHANGELOG.md` if **any** of these apply:

1. More than **2** distinct fixes/changes in the same task
2. One **global** setting or layout change (sidebar, session, navigation, defaults)
3. A **new feature** or user-facing capability

## Files to update together

- `egodary/_version.py` — `APP_VERSION` and `BUILD_NUMBER`
- `pyproject.toml` — `project.version`
- `egodary/api/main.py` — FastAPI `version=`
- `egodary/web/static/index.html` — footer version label (`vX.Y.Z`)
- `CHANGELOG.md` — add bullets under `[Unreleased]` (Added / Changed / Fixed)

## Changelog style

- Short, user-facing bullets in Russian or English (match surrounding entries)
- Mention UI moves, new buttons/icons, API endpoints when relevant
- Do not bump version for typo-only or comment-only edits
